</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 is located. 
The summit is accessible from the west via the town of El Cocuy, the village of Guicán and the hamlet of Las Cabaňas. The hike is fairly easy, but weather is not reliable, and a glacier must be crossed.
Because of global warming, 
<REF ID="693.3" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="np-subj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the Ritacuba Blanco</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Ritacuba Blanco's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the Ritacuba Blanco</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">its</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the Ritacuba Blanco's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the mountain's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 glacier is melting at very high rates, backing down 25 linear mts per year; same is happening at amazing speeds to all other snow-covered tropical mountains in Colombia. In 1950, 
<REF ID="693.4" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">its</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Ritacuba Blanco's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">its</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">the Ritacuba Blanco's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">the mountain's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 glacier extended down to 4,500 meters above sea level height; in January 2007 it lowest point was at 4,800 meters above sea level. If this melting rate continues, 
<REF ID="693.5" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Ritacuba Blanco's</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Ritacuba Blanco's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">its</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">the Ritacuba Blanco's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="common" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">the mountain's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 glacier is expected to disappear before 2025.</PARAGRAPH>
